modules.description: Generates Nano IDs using a time-seeded pseudo-random number generator. Provides the `nanoid` function to create IDs of a specified length, defaulting to 21 characters. Suitable for generating unique identifiers in distributed systems or logging contexts.

Generates Nano IDs using a customizable random number generator. It produces string identifiers of configurable length, defaulting to 21 characters. Useful for creating unique, URL-safe IDs in distributed systems or databases where collision resistance is critical.

Generates URL-safe, unique identifiers with customizable length and random number generation. Uses a provided RNG module to produce IDs, allowing seeded pseudo-random generation for reproducibility. Ideal for distributed systems needing collision-resistant IDs with controlled entropy sources.

Generates compact, URL-safe unique identifiers using a cryptographically secure random number generator. Works with string and integer types, allowing customization of the generated ID's length. Useful for creating unique keys in distributed systems, database records, or session identifiers.
